This paper deals with evolutionary algorithms and optimization problems, which are commonly studied in the subfield of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of mutation operators, which are relevant to the subfield of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper presents theoretical results on the optimization time, which falls under the subfield of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The problem classes studied in the paper involve component-wise minimization, which is a common topic in the subfield of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the representation of decision variables using multi-valued domains, which is relevant to the subfield of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
